Dear Hiring Team, 

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Entry-Level Full Stack Java Developer* role with *Cogent Infotech*. I bring over three years of professional experience in full-stack web applications, AI integration, and RESTful API development, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University.

Through my experience across multiple engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade backend systems that directly reflect *expertise in Full-Stack Java development, Spring Boot, and RESTful API design*. As a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I contributed to the development of an Identity & Access Management platform using *React*, *Spring Boot*, and *AWS*, supporting thousands of users across 30+ applications through seamless *Full Stack Integration*. I also built an internal support chatbot using *Java*, *LangChain*, and *RAG*, which reduced ticket resolution time by 20% by enabling *AI Integration* over internal documentation. These projects required rigorous *Quality Assurance* and the ability to develop backend workflows using *AWS Step Functions* and *Maven* to handle long-running data import jobs, ensuring operational stability and performance. More recently, at Sperse, I developed an *AI interaction layer* that translates *natural language processing* intents into validated tool calls across 1,000+ endpoints—a task that demanded the kind of *systems-level thinking and full-stack expertise this role demands*. Together, these roles have prepared me to *build scalable backend services and intuitive front-end interfaces that drive digital transformation* and drive impact within an agile engineering team.

My academic research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in model development and technical communication—skills that translate directly into *the passion for innovation, continuous learning, and adaptability that Cogent values*. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I conducted applied research on StyleGAN and Stable Diffusion using *PyTorch* and *LORA*, exploring *predictive modeling* concepts to enhance application capabilities. I was responsible for managing the full model development lifecycle—from training runs on HPC clusters to inference optimization using vLLM and deployment via Hugging Face—ensuring both performance and secure model serving. Beyond building the systems themselves, I have a strong commitment to professional growth and collaboration, as demonstrated by leading workshops on *AI Agents* for an audience of 50+ students. This experience has shaped me into an engineer who builds with rigor and communicates with clarity, directly mirroring *the focus on technical excellence and collaborative problem-solving* required for this position. I am eager to bring this same dedication to *Cogent Infotech and its mission to improve communities through technology*.

I have always been passionate about *building long-term relationships and delivering innovative digital solutions* and envision myself contributing my talent to the furthering of *digital transformation through emerging technologies*. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

